y drawings and etchings of K Laxma Goud.				 																																	 Till August 18 at names-AN.art (Gallery for Contemporary Art), 207A Rashbehari Avenue, near Bharat Sevasram Sangha/Bijon Setu; 3 pm - 7 pm: Paintings by Sekhar Kar.				 																																	 Till August 14 at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 2 pm - 8 pm: Paintings by Sudatta Basu Roy Chowdhury, Tutu Sarkar, Debika Mukherjee (Chattaraj), Dipak Kundu, Barun Roy and Utpal Naskar.				 																																	 Till August 20 at Genesis Art Gallery, 8B Middleton Street; 2 pm - 7 pm: Habitat Foundation presents an exhibition of paintings by The Ash Family  Gobardhan Ash, Nirban Ash, Deborshi Ash, Jyotirmoy Ash and Chinmoy Ash.				 																																	 Till August 22 (except August 15 amp; 16) at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 4 pm - 8 pm: Stroke and Chisel  an exhibition of the works of Sanatan Dinda, Subrata Gangopadhyay, Narendra Pal Singh, Ashutosh Nigam, Vijay Singh, Biman Das, Pradip Rakshit, Mohan Singh, Paresh Hazra, Noni Borpujari, Anant Nikam, S. Pranam Singh and Samit Dey.				 																																	 Till September 5 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: Paintings and sculptures by a group of renowned artists.PERFORMING ARTS				 																																	 August 13 at Bharatiyam, IB-201 Salt Lake; 6.30 pm: A programme of folk music featuring Nikhil Gayen and his group, Subal Das Bairagya Bahurupi, and the use of folk musical instruments like dotara, dhol, patar banshi, mridanga and matir hnari.				 																																	 August 14 at Rabindra Sadan; 6.15 pm: An evening of choreographic works, Salabhanjika (choreography: Pallavi Krishnan; produced by Lasya Dance Centre) and Ghungroo (choreography: Ashim Bandhu; produced by Upasana Centre for Dance).				 																																	 August 14 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: On its ninth anniversary, Samskritiki Shreyaskar will stage its premier show of Tagores Tasher Desh, a joint venture by Rani Karnaa with her disciples and associated artistes.				 																																	 August 18 at Rabindra Sadan; 6.30 pm: Tiyashi presents Parashkhani Bejechhilo Praner Taare  a solo recital of Tagore songs by Geeta Ghatak.				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 August 13 - 19 (except August 15) at Gorky Sadan; 4 pm - 7 pm: To celebrate the return of the Olympic Games to Greece, the cultural department of the Russian Federation Consulate General in Calcutta presents Glimpses of Greece  an exhibition of photographs by Mala Mukerjee. Inauguration today at 6 pm.				 																TALK				 																																	 August 13 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall; 6.15 pm: Swami Prabhananda will speak in Bengali on Amukhya Gita.				 																SEMINAR				 																																	 August 14 at Bangla Academy Sabhaghar; 6 pm: Kalyani Natyacharcha Kendra hosts a seminar on Contemporary Theatres in the Context of Socio-Political Scenario.				 																REUNION				 																																	 August 13 at Saturday Club; 8 pm: St James School Alumni Association is holding its sixth reunion dinner. Former principals J.A. Mason and D.L. Bloud will grace the occasion. Passes at Oasis Restaurant, 2229-9033 / 9831008657.				 																BOOKS				 																																	 Till August 16 at Oxford Bookstore, Park Street: A special exhibition on Oxford University Press titles. Categories: Non-fiction, dictionaries, anthology, sociology and economics.				 																ANTI-DRUG DRIVE				 																																	 August 13 at Kill Khana; 6.30 pm: As part of its anti-drug campaign, Calcutta Police, with the active participation of banglanatak.com, organises the street play, Jiban Phirey Esho.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 Till August 21 at Mrignayani, Dakshinapan, Dhakuria: Madhya Pra